3510 WARNING Cannot establish communication with [S]. [S].

optEvtDescription %parm[#1]%;

optEvtReported %parm[#2]%;

optEvtSent %parm[#3]%;

optEvtSeverity %parm[#4]%;
event.operinstruct:
All modules query periodically for transactions their primary CM. They record the transaction ID in their corresponding MOD_ROOT/transaction/state file, and after one cycle, the query again primary CM for transactions whose ID are higher than the ones at state.
Sometimes CM is not able to respond in a given timeout interval, and modules register this event in their logs.
As the modules connect every few seconds to CentralManager, the normal situation is that they will pick up new transactions in the following cycle if they were not able to do it in a particular moment in time. So these messages can be ignored unless they occur many times in a one minute interval. It will reveal that there is something wrong with ManagerTransaction.

event.operinstruct:
It does not imply saturation on CM or unattended requests. It simply means that in 60 seconds CM has received more than 100 requests for user->IP association, and hence above threshold has been passed.
If it is harmless, then, why is it reported? Well, in sites where traffic is not high, it could reveal a problem with content filtering modules users cache.
